                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Barrett</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-08-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Barrett reports that the minister for foreign affairs unofficially admits
                    that the Varilla letter practically settles the port question, but is not ready
                    to officially concede the same. As the minister for foreign affairs prefers that
                    negotiations toward a settlement of the question be continued here, Mr. Barrett
                    suggests that the Panama minister at Washington be advised in that sense.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
